import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]
    data['year'] = data['year'].dt.year

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wheat', data=data, label='Wheat Prices', marker='o')
    sns.lineplot(x='year', y='wages', data=data, label='Wages', marker='o')
    plt.title('What is the trend of wheat prices and wages over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Value')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(10, 6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='wheat', bins=20, kde=True, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['wheat'].median(), color='red', linestyle='--', label=f"Median: {data['wheat'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Wheat Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of wheat prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['year'])]

    avg_wheat = data['wheat'].mean()
    avg_wages = data['wages'].mean()

    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='year', y='wheat', ax=ax, label='Wheat Price')
    sns.scatterplot(data=data, x='year', y='wages', ax=ax, label='Wages')
    ax.axhline(avg_wheat, color='blue', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Wheat Price: {avg_wheat:.2f}')
    ax.axhline(avg_wages, color='orange', linestyle='--', label=f'Avg Wage: {avg_wages:.2f}')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.title('What is the average wheat price and wage over the entire dataset?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
